.START 

Sun Microsystems Inc., Mountain View, Calif., said it received a contract valued at about $97 million to provide computer workstations to the Ames Research Center, a field laboratory for the National Aeronautics and Space Administration. 

Under the seven-year contract, Sun said it will provide workstations using its Sparc microprocessor.
The Sparc chip, designed by Sun, incorporates reduced set computing, or RISC, techniques used in high-performance computers.
The machines will be used for scientific and aeronautical research, Sun said.
Deliveries are expected to begin next month, the company said. 

